    "spell": {
        "name": "Overflowing Sorrow",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "Sadness flows out of you into nearby creatures, blotting out any other thoughts they had. The first time a creature begins its turn in the area or enters the area, it must attempt a Will save. If it later leaves and reenters the area, it uses the same effect as before.",
